abstract: The invitation from Speaker Nancy Pelosi was notable because the president has lobbed insults at her in recent days for leading the House to approve two articles of impeachment.
snippet: The invitation from Speaker Nancy Pelosi was notable because the president has lobbed insults at her in recent days for leading the House to approve two articles of impeachment.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi invited President Trump to give the State of the Union address on Feb. 4, a sign that business is operating as usual in the nation’s capital, even after the House impeached the president two days ago.

abstract: Bomb-detection dogs sent by the United States to Jordan and Egypt got sick and in some cases died because of improper care, according to a State Department report released Friday.
snippet: Bomb-detection dogs sent by the United States to Jordan and Egypt got sick and in some cases died because of improper care, according to a State Department report released Friday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Bomb-detection dogs sent by the United States to Jordan and Egypt got sick and in some cases died because of improper care, according to a State Department report released Friday.
headline_main: Jordan, Egypt Faulted for Deaths of US-Trained Sniffer Dogs
headline_print_headline: Jordan, Egypt Faulted for Deaths of US-Trained Sniffer Dogs

abstract: An arbitrator correctly decided that the white Cleveland police officer who shot and killed Tamir Rice, a 12-year-old black child, should have been fired by the city for omissions on his city job application, a judge in Cleveland ruled.
snippet: An arbitrator correctly decided that the white Cleveland police officer who shot and killed Tamir Rice, a 12-year-old black child, should have been fired by the city for omissions on his city job application, a judge in Cleveland ruled.
lead_paragraph: CLEVELAND — An arbitrator correctly decided that the white Cleveland police officer who shot and killed Tamir Rice, a 12-year-old black child, should have been fired by the city for omissions on his city job application, a judge in Cleveland ruled.
headline_main: Judge Upholds Firing of Police Officer Who Killed Tamir Rice
headline_print_headline: Judge Upholds Firing of Police Officer Who Killed Tamir Rice

abstract: The Faroe Islands have become perhaps the most unexpected place for the United States and China to tussle over the Chinese tech giant Huawei.
snippet: The Faroe Islands have become perhaps the most unexpected place for the United States and China to tussle over the Chinese tech giant Huawei.
lead_paragraph: TORSHAVN, Faroe Islands — The mere existence of the Faroe Islands is a wonder. Tall peaks of snow-patched volcanic rock jut out from the North Atlantic Ocean. Steep cliffs plunge into the deep waters of narrow fjords.

abstract: Former Kentucky Gov. Matt Bevin defended his controversial pardon of a man who was convicted of raping a child, saying there was no physical evidence of an assault.
snippet: Former Kentucky Gov. Matt Bevin defended his controversial pardon of a man who was convicted of raping a child, saying there was no physical evidence of an assault.
lead_paragraph: LOUISVILLE, Ky. — Former Kentucky Gov. Matt Bevin defended his controversial pardon of a man who was convicted of raping a child, saying there was no physical evidence of an assault.
headline_main: Critics Attack Bevin's Pardon of Man Convicted of Child Rape
headline_print_headline: Critics Attack Bevin's Pardon of Man Convicted of Child Rape

abstract: After covering the Vietnam War and Washington, Mr. Just turned to writing novels that probed American society.
snippet: After covering the Vietnam War and Washington, Mr. Just turned to writing novels that probed American society.
lead_paragraph: Ward Just, a journalist for whom the Vietnam War was both a personal trauma and a national tragedy, inspiring him to write novels about people whose lives are shaped by war, political intrigue, myopic diplomats and various forces beyond their control, died on Thursday at a hospital in Plymouth, Mass. He was 84.

abstract: The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-voting states.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-votin...
lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — The Democratic National Committee is again upping its polling and fundraising requirements for presidential hopefuls to qualify for participating in the campaign's seventh debate in January, the first in a series of four held in the earliest-voting states.
headline_main: Party Again Ups Stakes for 7th Democratic Candidate Debate
headline_print_headline: Party Again Ups Stakes for 7th Democratic Candidate Debate
